content: I am a 4th-year Computer Science PhD student at UT Austin, co-advised by Işıl Dillig and Joydeep Biswas . I currently work on applying probabilistic program synthesis to robotics applications, and my past research has been mostly focusing on combining machine learning with programming language applications. Before joining UT, I received my bachelor’s degree in Physics from the University of Science and Technology of China. I was also a former intern at Facebook and JetBrains.
